ra Burlesque, Walking-Chair Design Studio, Peter Weinh\u00e4upl, Nives Widauer, Thomas Wohinz, [[Erwin Wurm]], Luisa Ziaja, and many more.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mak.at/en/salottovienna_-_brviennese_art_salon_in_trieste|title=SALOTTO.VIENNA - Viennese Art Salon in Trieste - MAK Museum Vienna|website=www.mak.at|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://diepresse.com/home/kultur/kunst/3853311/Salotto-Vienna_In-Triest-zeigt-sich-Wien-im-Salon Article by Johanna Hofleitner in] [[Die Presse]] (Austrian newspaper), August 8, 2014</ref><ref>[http://ilpiccolo.gelocal.it/tempo-libero/2014/08/24/news/salotto-vienna-stasera-parla-italiano-1.9809366 Article in] [[Il Piccolo]] (Italian newspaper), August 24, 2014</ref>\n* 2013, special project of the Vienna Art Week at [[Kunsthalle Wien]] Museumsquartier: Show by Berlin's legendary ''Club der polnischen Versager'' (Club of Polish Failures) produced by Marcello Farabegoli.<ref>[http://kunsthallewien.at/#/de/veranstaltungen/show-des-clubs-der-polnischen-versager Homepage of] [[Kunsthalle Wien]] (In German)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polnischeversager.de/vienna-art-week-2013-cpv-in-wien-kunsthalle-wien-museumsquartier-19-11-2013-um-1900-uhr/|title=VIENNA ART WEEK 2013 // CPV in Wien // Kunsthalle Wien Museumsquartier // 19.11.2013, um 19:00 Uhr|date=3 November 2013|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://www.falter.at/archiv/FALTER_2013111393E078A4B8/fiktive-polnische-oase-des-scheiterns Mention in] [[Falter]] (Austrian culture magazine), November 13, 2013</ref>\n* 2013, special project of the Vienna Art Week at [[Kunsthalle Wien]] Karlsplatz: presentation of catalogue ''Hana Usui \u2013 Drawings on paper 2006-2012'' by Eugenio d'Auria, Italian ambassador, and Monika Knofler, director of the Graphic Collection of the [[Academy of Fine Arts Vienna]]. Editor and producer of the event: Marcello Farabegoli.<ref>[http://kunsthallewien.at/#/de/veranstaltungen/katalogprasentation-hana-usui-drawings-paper-20062012 Homepage of] [[Kunsthalle Wien]] (In German)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hana-usui.net/kh-wien-12.html|title=KH Wien 12|website=www.hana-usui.net|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref>\n* 2008, Galerie oko ''\u2013'' Japanese Contemporary Art in Berlin: exhibition ''Murder of Oiran in Blood'' by [[Ushio Shinohara]] inaugurated by Antje Papist-Matsuo, research assistant at Kunsthistorisches Institut der [[Freie Universit\u00e4t Berlin|Freien Universit\u00e4t Berlin]], Hainz Stahlhut, director of the Fine Art Collection at the [[Berlinische Galerie]] - Berlin's State Museum of Modern Art, Photography & Architecture, and Marcello Farabegoli, director of Galerie oko.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ushioshinohara.com/?page_id=27|title=Artist statement|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hana-usui.net/shinohara.html|title=SHINOHARA|website=www.hana-usui.net|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mutualart.com/Artist/Ushio-Shinohara/DDF818E37A523841/Biography|title=Ushio Shinohara (Japanese, 1932) Full Biography - MutualArt|website=www.mutualart.com|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.de.emb-japan.go.jp/NaJ/NaJ0810/Kalender.htm|title=Kalender des Monats: Oktober 2008|website=www.de.emb-japan.go.jp|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.art-magazin.de/szene/9941/gib_mir_fuenf_die_tipps_der_woche|title=art - Das Kunstmagazin|website=Art Magazin|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://www.welt.de/welt_print/article2682360/Blutiger-Kurtisanen-Mord.html Article by Andrea Hilgenstock in] [[Die Welt]], (German newspaper), November 6, 2008</ref><ref>[https://www.neues-deutschland.de/artikel/137913.geborstenes-ganzes.html Article by Volkmar Draeger in] [[Neues Deutschland]] (German newspaper), October 27, 2008</ref>\n* 2007, Galerie oko ''\u2013'' Japanese Contemporary Art & Club der polnischen Versager (Club of Polish Failures