Sonntagszeitung]] (German newspaper), August 9, 2015</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artribune.com/report/2015/08/mostra-pioggia-nera-vienna-hana-usui-hiroshima/|title=Pioggia nera dopo la bomba. Hiroshima a Vienna - Artribune|first=Franco|last=Veremondi|date=19 August 2015|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://kurier.at/kultur/viennafair-neu-mit-schwankendem-niveau/157.177.986 Article by Michael Huber in] [[Kurier]] (Austrian newspaper), October 7, 2015</ref>\n* 2015, Italian embassy - Palais Metternich Vienna: exhibition ''Dance of Diplomacy - Transpositions'' by Sissa Micheli inaugurated by Giorgio Marrapodi, Italian ambassador, Manfred Matzka, secretary general of the Federal Chancellor Office representing Josef Ostermayer, Austrian Minister for Culture, Peter Bogner, director of the[[Frederick John Kiesler| Friedrich Kiesler]] Foundation, and Marcello Farabegoli, curator and producer of the exhibition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esteri.it/mae/en/sala_stampa/archivionotizie/approfondimenti/2015/05/vienna-all-ambasciata-prima-mostra.html/|title=Vienna - Italian Embassy hosts its first contemporary art exhibition|website=www.esteri.it|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artribune.com/television/2015/04/sissa-micheli-e-la-danza-della-diplomazia-una-mostra-allambasciata-italiana-a-vienna/|title=Sissa Micheli e la Danza della diplomazia. Una mostra all\u2019Ambasciata Italiana a Vienna - Artribune|first=Franco|last=Veremondi|date=22 April 2015|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://www.pressreader.com/italy/corriere-del-trentino/20150426/282252369074697 Article by Massimigliano Boschi in] [[Corriere del Trentino]] (Italian newspaper), April 26, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.altoadige.it/cultura-e-spettacoli/la-fotografa-sissa-micheli-a-palazzo-metternich-di-vienna-1.313776 Article in] [[Alto Adige (newspaper)|Alto Adige]] (Italian newspaper), April 26, 2015</ref>\n* 2014, special Project of the Vienna Art Week at Verein 08: exhibition ''No more Fukushimas'' with casaluce/geiger & Hana Usui, Julius Deutschbauer & Gabriel Sch\u00f6ller, Luca Faccio, Olga Georgieva, Shinshu Hida, [[Edgar Honetschl\u00e4ger]] & Sylvia Eckermann, Sissa Micheli, Takashi Ohno, Atsuko Otsuka, Federico Vecchi, and [[Erwin Wurm]]; Round table about nuclear energy with Judith Brandner, publicist and journalist at [[\u00d61]], Lucas Gehrmann, curator at [[Kunsthalle Wien]], Wolfgang Liebert, head of the Institute of Safety/Security and Risk Sciences at BOKU ([[University of Natural Resources and Life Sciences, Vienna]]), Patricia Lorenz, anti-nuclear campaigner GLOBAL 2000 \u2013 Friends of the Earth Austria, and Marcus Rennhofer, photovoltaic expert at AIT ([[Austrian Institute of Technology]]) / moderated by Tristan Jorde, actor; Curated and produced by Marcello Farabegoli.<ref>[http://derstandard.at/2000008436072/Reisbaellchen-aus-Fukushima Article by Anne Katrin Fe\u00dfler in] [[Der Standard]] (Austrian newspaper), November 20, 2014</ref><ref>[https://diepresse.com/home/kultur/kunst/4602199/Sieben-Tage-Visionen-fuer-den-Kunststandort-Wien Article by Sabine B. Vogel in] [[Die Presse]] (Austrian newspaper), November 23, 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.wienerzeitung.at/nachrichten/welt/weltpolitik/708432_Japan-liebaeugelt-wieder-mit-Atomkraft.html Article in] [[Wiener Zeitung]] (Austrian newspaper), November 18, 2014</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artribune.com/arti-visive/arte-contemporanea/2014/12/fukushima-mon-amour-la-mostra-dellanno-a-vienna/|title=Fukushima mon amour! La mostra dell\u2019anno a Vienna? - Artribune|first=Franco|last=Veremondi|date=6 December 2014|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://www.altoadige.it/cultura-e-spettacoli/la-mostra-viennese-di-farabegoli-1.173780 Article in] [[Alto Adige (newspaper)|Alto Adige]] (Italian newspaper), December 9, 2014</ref>\n* 2014,  ''Salotto.Vienna'' (Viennese Art Salon) at ex Pescheria \u2013 Salone deg